As of the [[census]] of 2020, there were 604 people and 228 households in the village. The population density was 1458.9 per sq mile . There were 243 housing units. The racial makeup of the village was 86% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 3% Asian and 10% a mix of any two races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1% of the population.

The median income for a household in the village was $60,278.  The [[per capita income]] for the village was $21,381. About 21% of families were below the [[poverty line]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Census profile: San Jose, IL |url=http://censusreporter.org/profiles/16000US1767613-san-jose-il/ |access-date=2025-06-21 |website=Census Reporter |language=en}}</ref>

